{{#each pools}}
{{#if isBoundary}}
`{{poolId}}` is referenced by ACL bindings, which makes it an enforcement boundary rather than a label: the identities
granted on `/pool/{{poolId}}` can see and act on guests **inside that pool and nowhere else**.
{{/if}}
{{/each}}
{{#each pools}}
{{#unless isBoundary}}
`{{poolId}}` is referenced by no grant at all, which is what keeps its members unreachable from any automation
credential.
{{/unless}}
{{/each}}

{{#if boundaryPools.length}}
> [!CAUTION]
> Adding a guest to {{{humanList boundaryPoolIds}}} silently grants every identity bound to that pool full access to
> it. Pool membership _is_ the permission — there is no second check.
{{/if}}

{{#if poolStorages.length}}
Storage-level membership is declared for {{{humanList poolStorages}}}, so the CSI plugin can provision volumes there.
Guest membership is not: it is set when Omni creates the VM, which is outside this stack.
{{/if}}
